9","1558":"1558","about 1549":"circa 1549","1577":"1577","1484":"1484","about 1577":"circa 1577","about 1484":"circa 1484","1549":"1549","before 1504":"vóór 1504","1504":"1504","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","Sandridge, Hertfordshire, England":"Sandridge, Hertfordshire, England","England":"England","Deddington, Oxfordshire, England":"Deddington, Oxfordshire, England"},"en":{"about 1484–about 1577":"about 1484–about 1577","1484–1549":"1484–1549","1504–1577":"1504–1577","1484–1577":"1484–1577","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","about 1549":"about 1549","1577":"1577","1484":"1484","about 1577":"about 1577","about 1484":"about 1484","1549":"1549","before 1504":"before 1504","1504":"1504","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","Sandridge, Hertfordshire, England":"Sandridge, Hertfordshire, England","England":"England","Deddington, Oxfordshire, England":"Deddington, Oxfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Joane","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: altered form of   Jean  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Jean","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Pierre, Francois, Marcel, Yves, Andre, Jacques, Georges, Michel, Philippe, Serge, Yvon, Cecile.","French, Walloon, West Indian (mainly Haiti), Mauritian, and English (of French Huguenot origin): from the male personal name <i>Jean</i>, French form of   John  . This is one of the most frequent surnames in Haiti (along with   Joseph   and   Pierre  ). It is also established elsewhere in the West Indies (e.g. in the Dominican Republic, Saint Lucia, Saint Martin, and Bahamas).","English: habitational name for someone from Genoa in Italy; compare   Janeway  ."]}]},{"name":"South","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>south</i> ‘south’, denoting someone who had migrated ‘from the south’, especially someone from southern England living in the north of the country. It may also have been used as a topographic name to denote someone living in the southern part of a settlement or region. Compare   Southern  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Suderman","meanings":["Americanized form of German <b>Sudermann</b>: topographic name for someone living to the south of a settlement or for an incomer from the south, from Middle Low German <i>sūder</i> ‘south’ + <i>man</i> ‘man’. Compare   South  ."]},{"name":"Southern","meanings":["English (Lancashire): nickname from Middle English <i>s(o)uthern(e)</i>, <i>sothron</i> ‘southern’ (Old English <i>sūtherne</i>, Old Norse <i>suthrænn</i>), for someone ‘from the south’, particularly as a northern English nickname for someone from the south of the country and as a Scottish nickname for an Englishman."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":65,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":74,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":85,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Joane South was born about 1484, in England. She married Robert Kinkey before 1504, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died about 1577, in Oxfordshire, England, at the age of 95."},"et":{"about 1484–about 1577":"umbes 1484–umbes 1577","1484–1549":"1484–1549","1504–1577":"1504–1577","1484–1577":"1484–1577","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","about 1549":"umbes 1549","1577":"1577","1484":"1484","about 1577":"umbes 1577","about 1484":"umbes 1484","1549":"1549","before 1504":"enne 1504","1504":"1504","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","Sandridge, Hertfordshire, England":"Sandridge, Hertfordshire, England","England":"England","Deddington, Oxfordshire, England":"Deddington, Oxfordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1484–about 1577":"noin 1484–noin 1577","1484–1549":"1484–1549","1504–1577":"1504–1577","1484–1577":"1484–1577","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","about 1549":"noin 1549","1577":"1577","1484":"1484","about 1577":"noin 1577","about 1484":"noin 1484","1549":"1549","before 1504":"ennen vuotta 1504","1504":"1504","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","Sandridge, Hertfordshire, England":"Sandridge, Hertfordshire, England","England":"England","Deddington, Oxfordshire, England":"Deddington, Oxfordshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1484–about 1577":"environ 1484–environ 1577","1484–1549":"1484–1549","1504–1577":"1504–1577","1484–1577":"1484–1577","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","about 1549":"environ 1549","1577":"1577","1484":"1484","about 1577":"environ 1577","about 1484":"environ 1484","1549":"1549","before 1504":"avant 1504","1504":"1504","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Angleterre","Sandridge, Hertfordshire, England":"Sandridge, Hertfordshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","Deddington, Oxfordshire, England":"Deddington, Oxfordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Joane South est née environ 1484, à Angleterre. Elle a épousé Robert Kinkey avant 1504, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. El